T2	p 64 745	Electronic biosensors to detect even a single Xylella fastidiosa bacterium quickly, before the effects are visible, thus allowing more effective interventions. This is the objective of a study carried out by researchers of the Institute for the Sustainable Protection of Plants (Cnr-Ipsp) and of the Institute of Photonics and Nanotechnology (Cnr-Ifn) of the National Research Council, in collaboration with the Departments of Chemistry, Pharmacy-Drug Sciences and Physics of the University of Bari, and with the contribution of Agritest S.r.l. The results of the research have been published in Advanced Science, a prestigious international journal with a very high impact factor.
