T10	p 2061 2600	“At the moment, the early detection of the bacterium and the containment measures implemented in the regional territories seem to have slowed down the spread of the bacterium. We need rapid and reliable tools to diagnose and intervene early trying to stop the disease, for which no cures capable of healing infected plants have so far been found", continues Donato Boscia, head of the Bari branch of the Institute for the Sustainable Protection of Plants (Cnr-Ipsp) and among the pioneers in the fight against Xylella fastidiosa in Puglia.
