T12	p 2601 3059	The obtained result has great relevance for the early detection of plant pathogenic organisms and for the implementation of preventive measures. "For example, biosensors based on single-molecule transistor (SiMoT) technology have the concrete prospect of being used for diagnostics in the field of plant pest diseases", says Eleonora Macchia, researcher in the Department of Pharmacy-Drug Sciences of the 'University of Bari, winner of an ERC Starting Grant.
